title.narrative: Reproductive Child Health Programme Phase II I Technical Assistance

description.narrative: This activity (Reproductive Child Health Programme Phase II I Technical Assistance) is a component of Reproductive and Child Health Programme Phase II reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £8,868,919. This component benefits India, and works in the following sector(s): Health policy and administrative management, Reproductive health care. , with the following implementing partners: CARE International UK, Crown Agents Limited, Deloitte Touche Tohmatsu India LLP, IPE Global Private Limited, Liverpool School of Tropical Medicine, London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine, Management Sciences For Health, Inc., Mott MacDonald Limited. The start date is 15-12-2006 and the end date is 30-09-2013.
